Before a molder may sell the die, mold, form, or pattern, the molder shall notify the customer by registered mail, return receipt requested. The notice shall include:
The molder's intention to sell the die, mold, form, or pattern thirty (30) days after the customer's receipt of the notice;
A description of the die, mold, form, or pattern to be sold;
The time and place of the sale; and
An itemized statement for the amount due.
